com.mobius.vdrapi
Class EnhancedSearchTopicItemQueryParam

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.mobius.vdrapi.QueryParam

        +--com.mobius.vdrapi.EnhancedSearchTopicItemQueryParam
public class EnhancedSearchTopicItemQueryParam
extends QueryParam

This class provides the ability to submit enhanced topic item searches with a VdrSearchExpression search expression that contains VdrSearchTerm search terms joined by either AND or OR.

The constructors of this class verify that the search terms submitted contain operators acceptable for this query. These operators are:

  • Equals (EQ)
  • Not Equals (NE)
  • Less Than (LT)
  • Less Than or Equal To (LE)
  • Greater Than (GT
  • Greater Than or Equal To (GE)
  • Between (BT)
  • Not Between (NB)
  • Like (LK)
An OperatorNotSupportedException exception will be thrown if an ineligible operator is found within a search expression's search terms. A ParsingException exception will be thrown if invalid search term is found in the search Expression

Search Example:

(SectionId LessThanOrEqualTo "0003") AND ("ACCOUNTCD" GreaterThan "0")

Create Search Terms

SectionSearchTerm term1 = new SectionSearchTerm( ComparisonOperators.LE ,"0003");
TopicSearchTerm term2 = new TopicSearchTerm("ACCOUNTCD", ComparisonOperators.GT ,"0");

Create a Search Expression (joined by AND)

VdrSearchExpression andSearchExp = VdrSearchExpression.createAndExpression();
SearchExpr.addTerm(term1);
SearchExpr.addTerm(term2);

Create an EnhancedSearchTopicItemQueryParam

QueryParam qParam = new EnhancedSearchTopicItemQueryParam(SearchExpr, requestCount);

Create instance of SearchTopicItemListFactory

SearchTopicItemListFactory sti = session.createListFactory(SessionFactoryType.SearchTopicItems);
Submit the query

INode[] enodes = sti.createList(qParam);
